      "id": 23254,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "**CVE-2020-13487** | The bbPress plugin through 2.6.4 for WordPress has stored XSS in the Forum creation section, resulting in JavaScript execution at *wp-admin/edit.php?post_type=forum* (aka the Forum listing page) for all users. An administrator can exploit this at the *wp-admin/post.php?action=edit* URI.",
